Every year I follow the applications for @si_swimsuit as they flood my feed, and I’m SO excited to share that this year I’ve finally submitted my own video to be in the running for the SI 2023 swim search.🥰🤞🏻

I was born in FL and grew up in Panama (Republic of Panama 🇵🇦 not Florida 😛)so the beach is truly one of my favorite places. When I was 16 I was diagnosed with severe scoliosis and quickly became extremely insecure with my body and how others viewed it. I had doctors telling me that my only option at that point was to get spinal fusion surgery, which did not feel right for me so I threw myself into alternative methods of treatment. 

Over the years I’ve been blessed to work with the most incredible doctors and I’ve learned to love my curve(s).🥰 I’m 29 and most people would never guess I have a 60 degree curve and this is thanks to a LOT of hard work and dedication, but totally worth it. All in all through this journey I’ve learned 3 important lessons that I hope to pass on to anyone else going through a similar situation:

1. Just because something is a part of you doesn’t mean it defines you.
2. Scoliosis is more than a diagnosis - it’s a lifestyle! Daily stretches and exercises are essential to stay out of pain and keep my curve mobile under control. I use to hate it but now I think of it as a blessing because it keeps me active. 
3. Finding ways to turn a hardship into an inspiration is just as healing for yourself as it is a tool to help others. 

I hope I get the honor to meet @mj_day and the rest of the SI family in 2023 and take part in a movement where I can inspire others to love their bodies no matter what. It's not easy and it does not happen over night, but I am proof you can embrace the challenges(blessings) life throws at you. 💚 

#siswimsearch2023 @theswimfluencenetwork
